\dfrac2\pi\int_0^{\pi/2}\sqrt{t^2+r^2-2tr\cos(\alpha)}\,\mathrm  d\alpha
r \approx t
t=1
r=1
I(r)
r=1
 I(r)=\int _0 ^{\pi/2} \sqrt{1+{r}^{2} -2\,r\,{\cos}\left( \theta \right) } ~d\theta 
 2 \int _0 ^{\pi/2} \sin(\theta/2) ~d\theta = 4 -2 \sqrt{2} 
 \frac{d I(r)}{dr}= \int_0 ^{\pi/2} \frac{r-{\cos}\left( \theta\right) }{\sqrt{1+{r}^{2} -2\,r\,{\cos}\left( \theta \right) }} ~d\theta 
 \left. \frac{d I(r)}{dr}\right|_{r=1}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \int_0 ^{\pi/2} \sqrt{1-\cos(\theta)} ~d\theta = 2-\sqrt{2} 
I(r) \approx 4 - 2\sqrt{2} +(2-\sqrt{2})(r-1)
I(r) \approx t ~\left(4 - 2\sqrt{2} +(2-\sqrt{2})(r/t-1)\right) = (2-\sqrt(2)) (t+r)
 \hbox{answer} ~\approx~ \frac{4-2\sqrt{2}}{\pi} (t+r) 
